# Migrations

Database schema migrations managed by Alembic.

## How it works

Schema is defined in `app/db/models.py` using SQLAlchemy declarative models.
Alembic diffs the models against the live database and generates migration files automatically.

LangGraph's checkpoint tables (`checkpoints`, `checkpoint_blobs`, `checkpoint_writes`) are
excluded from autogenerate — they are managed by `checkpointer.setup()` at startup.

## Commands

Run from the `backend/` directory.

```bash
# Apply all pending migrations
make migrate

# Auto-generate a new migration after editing models.py
make migration name="describe_what_changed"

# Check current migration state
.venv/bin/alembic current

# View migration history
.venv/bin/alembic history

# Rollback one migration
.venv/bin/alembic downgrade -1

# Rollback all migrations
.venv/bin/alembic downgrade base
```

## Workflow

1. Edit `app/db/models.py` — add a table, column, index, etc.
2. Run `make migration name="add_user_id_to_conversations"`
3. Review the generated file in `migrations/versions/`
4. Run `make migrate` to apply

## Versions

| Revision | Description |
|---|---|
| `0001` | Create conversations table |
